Subject: Re: [T2] what happens if you don't change your oil in 10,000

On Wednesday, March 23, 2005, at 04:40PM, Mike Soultanian <msoultan(-at-)csulb.edu> wrote:

>Granted, I've 
>probably gone at least 4k if I did change it somewhere in there, but 
>that's still better than 10k!

VW recommends 7,500 miles between changes so I don't think you have to worry much.

>So, I was curious what are the signs of unchanged oil?

It's hard to tell because it goes black so quickly. Unless it's become black and runny or turned to a thick sludge you'd probably have to send it off for analysis.

>Is there anything I should look for in particular?

Drop the strainer and look for sludge from the bearings.

